  "instructions": [
    "In a small pot, combine rinsed chickpeas, diced tomatoes, garlic, cumin, salt, and 1 tbsp water. Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes until slightly thickened.",
    "While chickpeas cook, heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a pan and sauté 2 pita breads until golden on both sides.",
    "Add lemon juice to the chickpea mixture and stir until well combined.",
    "Fold in chopped parsley and serve immediately over the warm pita breads.",
    "Adjust seasoning to taste with additional salt or lemon juice if needed."
